content:
Launch OmniScripts from Lightning and Experience Pages

The generated OmniScript component:

* Automatically passes the RecordId for the page into the OmniScript's Data JSON in the ContextId node
* Displays the Lightning layout
* Is URL addressable independently or through the Experience or Lightning page URL
* Can accept parameters such as prefill

Add an OmniScript to a Lightning or Experience Cloud Page
Add an OmniScript to a Lightning or Experience Cloud page by adding the OmniScript's generated Lightning web component.

Display Inline OmniScripts on Lightning and Experience CloudPages
Enable OmniScripts to run inline without leaving the context of a page. An inline OmniScript renders as a button that, when clicked, launches the OmniScript inline.

Add a Standard OmniScript Component to a Lightning Page or Add a Standard OmniScript Component to Experience CloudPages 
Run an OmniScript in standard runtime. From the Lightning Builder or Aura-based Experience Builder, add the standard OmniScript component to a page.

Deploy, Launch, and Embed OmniScripts
title: Launch and Deploy OmniScripts
